alluxio.client.block

Class RetryHandlingBlockWorkerClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • alluxio.AbstractThriftClient<BlockWorkerClientService.Client>
      • alluxio.client.block.RetryHandlingBlockWorkerClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BlockWorkerClient, Closeable, AutoCloseable

    @ThreadSafe
public final class RetryHandlingBlockWorkerClient
extends AbstractThriftClient<BlockWorkerClientService.Client>
implements BlockWorkerClient
    The client talks to a block worker server. It keeps sending keep alive message to the worker server. Since BlockWorkerClientService.Client is not thread safe, this class has to guarantee thread safety.

        public RetryHandlingBlockWorkerClient(WorkerNetAddress workerNetAddress,
                                      Long sessionId)

        Creates a RetryHandlingBlockWorkerClient. Set sessionId to null if no session Id is required when using this client. For example, if you only call RPCs like promote, a session Id is not required.
        Parameters:
        workerNetAddress - to worker's location
        sessionId - the id of the session
        Throws:
        IOException - if it fails to register the session with the worker specified
